  <p>TO INCLUDE A <b>BREADCRUMB</b> COMPONENT:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      Create a nav element with nested list element - ordered or unordered. Include any desired attributes and content.
    </li>
    <pre>&lt;nav&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/nav&gt;</pre>
    <li>
      Add the one or more Kickstart classes, separated by spaces, to the element using the class attribute. Also
      add class
      <pre>breadcrumb-nav</pre>
      or
      <pre>process-breadcrumb</pre>
      for step by step actions.
      for badges.
    </li>
    <pre>&lt;nav class=&quot;breadcrumb-nav&quot;&gt;&lt;ol class=&quot;breadcrumb&quot;&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/nav&gt;</pre>
    <pre>&lt;nav class=&quot;process-breadcrumb&quot;&gt;&lt;ol class=&quot;breadcrumb&quot;&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/nav&gt;</pre>
    <li>
      List items in
      <pre>breadcrumb-nav</pre>
      will behave as simple breadcrumb, list items
      <pre>process-breadcrumb</pre>
      will behave as step by step breadcrumbs.
    </li>
  </ol>
  <p>CONFIGURATION OPTIONS</p>
  <p>The Kickstart CSS classes apply various predefined visual enhancements to the badge. The table below lists
    the available classes and their effects.</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Class</th>
      <th>Effect</th>
      <th>Remarks</th>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><span><pre>breadcrumb-nav</pre></span></td>
      <td>Defines breadcrumb nav component</td>
      <td>Required on a nav element<br>Mutually exclusive with
        <pre>.process-breadcrumb</pre>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span><pre>process-breadcrumb</pre></span></td>
      <td>Defines process breadcrumb nav component</td>
      <td>Required on a nav element<br>Mutually exclusive with
        <pre>.process-breadcrumb</pre>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><span><pre>breadcrumb</pre></span></td>
      <td>Defined list for containing the breadcrumb items.</td>
      <td>Required on a list element - ol/ul</td>
    </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
